For Testing the RobertsFlow trought accelerations.
Remember to compile at least:
./configure "--with-equation-of-state=isothermal-gas --with-forcing=roberts-flow-acceleration"
Files>
./makeIC_TestAccel.py
(generates the IC from a glass file, check the B0=0 and v0=0, to check the
forcing trough Accelerations. There are Vector potencial and Bfield even if
not used, because of the MHD nature of the test)
./RF_TestAccel.yml
(parameter file for swift. Important parameters:
RobertsFlowAccelerationForcing:
  u0:                   0.375
  Vz_factor:            0.0
  nu:                   1.0
EoS:
  isothermal_internal_energy: 100.0
  
Also need to play with timesteping and viscosity alpha. This file contains the
parameters for the run shown in the wiki.)
./pplot_TestAccel.py [folder]
(plots density / MHD stuff not needed / and velocity projections of the folder) 
./energy_TestAccel.py [statistics.txt file]
(flots the angular and linear momentum evolution of the run)

